"{\n  \"diabetes_mellitus\": {\n    \"Type 1 Diabetes\": {\n      \"description\": \"Type 1 diabetes is an autoimmune condition where the body's immune system attacks and destroys insulin-producing beta cells in the pancreas, typically occurring in childhood or adolescence.\"\n    },\n    \"Type 2 Diabetes\": {\n      \"description\": \"Type 2 diabetes is characterized by insulin resistance and progressive decline in insulin secretion, often linked to lifestyle factors and genetics, and commonly diagnosed in adults.\"\n    },\n    \"Gestational Diabetes\": {\n      \"description\": \"Gestational diabetes is a form of diabetes that develops during pregnancy in women who did not previously have diabetes, impacting glucose metabolism and requiring careful management.\"\n    },\n    \"MODY (Maturity-Onset Diabetes of the Young)\": {\n      \"description\": \"MODY is a rare, genetically determined form of diabetes typically diagnosed before age 25, often caused by mutations in single genes affecting insulin production or action.\"\n    },\n    \"Latent Autoimmune Diabetes in Adults (LADA)\": {\n      \"description\": \"LADA, also known as Type 1.5 diabetes, is a slowly progressive form of autoimmune diabetes occurring in adults, sharing characteristics of both Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes.\"\n    }\n  }\n}"